{"name": "Chanakya Neeti", "id": 250, "content": "<p><em>A collection of writings from <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chanakya\" target=\"_blank\">Chanakya</a>. He basically talks about what a person should do for a good social life. Some of the things are still relevant, others might have become obsolete.</em></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Things which cause problem for a person:</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Advising fools, Caretaking/keeping a <strong><em>spoiled woman</em></strong>, keeping company of negative/suffering people. <em>[All these terms need a definition though: fool, spoiled, negative]</em></p>\n\n<p>Spoiled wife, Mean/abject friends, disobedient servant, snake</p>\n\n<p>Of a rascal and a serpent, the serpent is the better of the two, for he strikes only at the time he is destined to kill, while the former at every step.</p>\n\n<p>Do not keep company with a fool for as we can see he is a two-legged beast. Like an unseen thorn he pierces the heart with his sharp words.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Wealth:</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>Accumulation of wealth for possible adverse future.</p>\n\n<p>Priority: Self &gt; Protection of woman &gt; Wealth</p>\n\n<p>(Even accumulation goes away some time)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Where should a person live?</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Presence of these things required :</p>\n\n<p>Respect, Occupation, Friendship and brotherhood, Means of education</p>\n\n<p>Prosperous businessmen/traders, Ved-following brahmans (or, <em>intellectuals in todays world</em>), Just, politically able ruler (or, <em>leaders in today&#39;s world</em>), Rivers, Doctors</p>\n\n<p>Trade/Business, Penalty-system, social-shaming (or maybe social-credit) system, Wisdom, Cleverness</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Who is true X?</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Friend, brother -&nbsp; who helps in the times of disease, troublehood, fear of enemy, death of relatives.</p>\n\n<p>Wife - who is with you even in destitute conditions.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>What is a Good X?</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Son - obedient, Father - who can raise, nourish child, Wife - who gives happiness, Friend - who is trustworthy, and not a betrayer.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Responsibility:</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>Give your daughter in marriage to a good family, engage your son in learning, see that your enemy comes to grief, and engage your friends in dharma.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Risk Aversion</strong></em></p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Definite vs Speculative/Probable:&nbsp;</strong></em>Take definite. <em>[Does this imply Instant Gratification instead of Deferred Gratification]</em></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Caste and Women</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>A. Not so beautiful, but from a noble caste</p>\n\n<p>B. Beautiful, but from lower caste</p>\n\n<p>Give priority to A.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Trust</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>Don&#39;t trust: Nailed violent animals, Rivers, Horned animals, Weapon-holders, Women, Royal people</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Doesn&#39;t Matter Where Good Thing Comes From</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>Take Elixir from Poison, Gold from impure substances, Wisdom/knowledge from mean/abject person, Good woman from low caste.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Men vs Women</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Woman - 2x nutrition/food, 4x intellect/intelligence, 6x bravery, 8x Lust</p>\n\n<p><em>[Seems dubious]</em></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Nature of Women</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Liars, Brave, Deceivers,&nbsp;chameleon, Greedy, Impure, Non-compassionate</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Prosperity</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>of food, luxury, women for satiation come to man either by fruits of past lives, or by [extreme] hard work.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Heaven on Earth</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Obedient son,</p>\n\n<p>Wife -&nbsp; compatible, faithful, satisfied with current possession</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Trust Regardin Secrets</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>No one - Even a good friend can spill the beans</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Secrecy of Strategy/Plan</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Keep the plan to yourself, and execute silently</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Education</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Parents who don&#39;t educate their children are actually their enemies. No education =&gt; No respect among educated.</p>\n\n<p>Though men be endowed with beauty and youth and born in noble families, yet&nbsp;without education they are like the palasa flower, which is void of sweet fragrance.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Strictness vs Softness</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Children, Disciples/students get spoiled with much softness, so strictness is required.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Things which burn the body</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Separation from wife, Disrespect from relatives, Debt, Service of cruel/unjust ruler.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Power</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Power of Intellectuals in Knowledge&nbsp;Rulers &rarr;&nbsp;Army, Traders&nbsp;&rarr; Money, Uneducated&nbsp;&rarr; Service</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Saints and Good People</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>At the time of the pralaya (universal destruction) the oceans are to exceed their limits and seek to change, but a saintly man never changes.</p>\n\n<p>The beauty of a cuckoo is in its notes, that of a woman in her unalloyed devotion to her husband, that of an ugly person in his scholarship, and that of an ascetic in his forgiveness.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>Guesthood</em></strong></p>\n\n<p>Just have a meal and get away just like Prostitues get away from poor, Citizens get away from defeated/powerless ruler, Birds get away from fruitless trees.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Happiness and Sorrow</strong></em></p>\n\n<p>In this world, whose family is there without blemish? Who is free from sickness and grief? Who is forever happy?</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>A man&#39;s descent may be discerned by his conduct, his country by his pronunciation of language, his friendship by his warmth and glow, and his capacity to eat by his body.</p>\n\n<p><br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n", "authorId": 1, "subject": "philosophy", "tags": [], "img": "", "summary": "", "lastUpdated": "2021-04-25 13:44:58.089449"}